Peptide Data Template

May 11, 2021

Upload Data

Expression Data

An unlabelled peptide expression data file called “pep_edata.csv” was uploaded to pmart. The column that designates unique molecules was marked as “Mass_Tag_ID”. The original scale of the data was raw intensity and was transformed to log2. The value to denote missing data was “NA” and the expression data was not normalized.

Biomolecule Information

An associated biomolecule information file was also uploaded called “pep_emeta.csv” and the protein identifier column was designated as “Protein”.

Group Samples

Sample Information

An associated sample information file was also uploaded called “pep_fdata.csv”. This metadata file does contain peptide to protein mappings. Trimmed sample names were not used. The column in the sample information file which indicates sample names was designated as “SampleID”.

Filter

Filters were applied.

Summary of Applied Filters

Filter Type Parameters
Molecule Filter Biomolecule Molecule Number Min: 2
CV Filter Biomolecule Max CV: 150
imd-ANOVA Filter Biomolecule ANOVA Min: 2 & G-test Min: 3
Proteomics Filter Biomolecule Peptide Number Min: 2 & Remove Degenerates: Yes
rMD Filter Sample P-Value Threshold: 0.001 & Outlier Metrics: MAD, Kurtosis, Skewness, Correlation
Custom Filter Sample Samples with Infection5 were removed.

Molecule Filter

A molecule filter was applied. A molecule filter was applied to the data, removing Mass_Tag_IDs that were present in fewer than 2 samples. A total of 1814 Mass_Tag_IDs were filtered out of the dataset by this filter.

CV Filter

A CV filter was applied. A coefficient of variation (CV) filter was applied to the data, removing Mass_Tag_IDs with a CV greater than 150. A total of 2 Mass_Tag_IDs were filtered out of the dataset by this filter.

imd-ANOVA Filter

A imd-ANOVA filter was applied. An ANOVA filter was applied to the data, removing Mass_Tag_IDs that do not have at least 2 non-missing values per group. Additionally, an IMD (independence of missing data) filter was applied to the data, removing Mass_Tag_IDs that do not have at least 3 non-missing values in at least one of the groups specified in the group_DF attribute of the dataset. A total of 1861 Mass_Tag_IDs were filtered out of the dataset by this filter.

Proteomics Filter

A proteomics filter was applied. A degenerate peptide filter was applied to the data, identifying Mass_Tag_IDs that map to more than one Protein. The filter identified 0 such Mass_Tag_IDs in the data. Associated with these Mass_Tag_IDs were 0 Proteins that no longer had Mass_Tag_IDs mapping to them. Additionally, a protein filter was applied to the data, identifying Proteins that do not have at least 2 Mass_Tag_IDs mapping to them. This filter identified 952 Proteins from the data. Associated with these Proteins were 708 Mass_Tag_IDs that no longer mapped to a Protein. Together, the two filters removed 708 Mass_Tag_IDs and 952 Proteins from the data.

rMD Filter

A rMD filter was applied. A robust Mahalanobis distance (rMd) filter was applied to the data, removing SampleIDs with an rMd-associated p-value less than 0.001. A total of 1 SampleIDs were filtered out of the dataset by this filter.

Custom Filter

A custom filter was applied. A custom filter was applied to the data, removing 0 Mass_Tag_IDs from e_data, 0 Proteins from e_meta, and 1 SampleIDs from f_data.

Normalization

Peptide data was normalized.

Manual

Manual normalization was used to normalize the data.
